\i \cf0 Jesus led them up on a high mountain, the three
\i0 \
Given a unique experience.\
Jesus had said \'93there are some standing here who shall not taste death till they see the Son of Man coming in His Kingdom\'94.\
The term \'93Son of Man\'94.\
Used all through the Gospels. Why? Why this term?\
Essentially it simply expresses His relationship to man.\
\

\i In a deeper sense
\i0 , we must remember, God entered time and space through the agency of the Holy Spirit, through which the virgin conceived, and Jesus was born, like all men, yet he bypassed as it were, the curse we inherit, and is born sinless, yet he is man. Or, Son of Man.\
He is also Son of God, in two senses.\
One, as the eternal Son of God, the Second member of the Trinity.\
Two, as a direct creation of God.\
\

\i Let me explain a bit
\i0 \
In Lk 3:23-38 we can see the geneology of Jesus, from birth going backwards to Adam. \
Where is that last verse, v38, it says, \'93the son of Enosh, the son of Seth, the son of Adam, the son of God\'94.\
Here, the bible says that Adam, is the son of God.\
In what sense?\
Because, Adam came into being as a direct creation of God. A son of God.\
He had no human father.\
Example. Adam is not the only example.\
The angels are often called sons of God because they too were created directly by God.\
They awoke to existence and were completely created.\
Job 1:6, 2:1 and 38:7 \'93when the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy\'94. \'96 Creation.\
And what about us, as new creations, directly from God, born again through His Spirit.\
Jn 1:12 \'93But as many as received Him, to them He gave the right to become children (sons \'96 KJV) of God, to those who believe in His Name\'94.\
\

\i Jesus is born of a woman
\i0 , Gal 4:4, He is THE Son of God, and is THE Son of Man.\
It is the \'93Son of Man coming in His Kingdom\'94\
This is the promised Kingdom.\
This is the Kingdom originally intended for man.\
This is what the first Adam lost.\
This is what the last Adam gives.\
And as Son of Man, He represents man, and this kingdom is for us.\
\
Now we need to bear in mind there are two aspects to this kingdom.\
First, there will be a literal 1000 year reign on earth, this is what this passage is about.\
The Kingdom of God on earth, also known as the earthly kingdom.\
Where Jesus Christ will reign on a literal throne in Jerusalem for 1000 years.\
Second, at the end of the 1000 years, time itself will be done away with and the Glory of the Kingdom will be followed by eternity.\
